news.title: Market value of land in new Andhra Pradesh districts to see upward revision
news.para: Sensing that the number of land registrations have already picked up pace in the new district headquarters, the government has decided to mop up additional revenue by increasing the market value of land.

news.title: Land diverted via 22,000 illegal registries in Gurugram division in four years: Probe
news.para: Of these, more than 15,000 were in Gurgaon district alone. Through the illegal registries, land notified as a controlled area – which has certain safeguards – was diverted for construction, officials said.

news.title: Nuvoco Vistas Corp to invest Rs 1,950 crore as part of expansion plans
news.para: Besides, Nuvoco Vistas will invest Rs 400 crore on debottlenecking and upgradation of projects at its existing plants and Rs 50 crore to set up alternate fuel material handling facilities.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Rs 1 crore cash found in income tax searches on developers
news.para: “About 50 officers and 100 staff members participated in the searches. They were brought from the major cities of Gujarat. Three brokers associated with the companies are also under scrutiny," said a source.

news.title: No occupier can acquire land title by adverse possession: Madras HC
news.para: The occupier can plead and prove title by adverse possession only as long as the government property remains as a government poramboke, not being reserved for any public purposes.

news.title: Sale of Lutyens bungalow under Delhi HC lens
news.para: Punit Beriwala, the Vipul MD, moved the high court after Bhai Manjit Singh’s lawyer issued a public notice of sale. Beriwala claimed that the property cannot be sold to anyone else since he had made an advance payment.

news.title: Mindspace REIT's net operating income up 4% to Rs 371.5 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Mindspace Business Parks REIT CEO Vinod Rohira said the company witnessed a significant uptick of leasing activity with around 1.8 million square feet of space leased in the December quarter, taking the overall leasing to around 3.8 million square feet the first nine months of FY22.

news.title: Delhi HC reserves order on bail plea by Ambience Group's promoter
news.para: The ED had earlier raided Gehlot, his company Aman Hospitality Private Limited (AHPL), some other firms of the Ambience group, director in the company Dayanand Singh, Mohan Singh Gehlot, and their associates.

news.title: Gurugram: Portion of building in Chintels Paradiso collapses, one dead
news.para: The official said the dining room floor of a sixth-floor apartment at Chintels Paradiso housing complex first came down, triggering the collapse of roofs and floors directly under it, till the first floor.

news.title: Barratt's pre-tax profit rises 0.6% to $586.30 million
news.para: Barratt Chief Executive Officer David Thomas said that increased levels of household savings during the pandemic had helped consumers reassess their options, leading to higher transaction levels, and purchasing power has stayed strong.

news.title: Property ladder too high for central Europe's first-time buyers
news.para: The Czech Republic ranks as the least affordable housing market in Europe with an average of 12.2 gross annual salaries needed to buy a 70-square-metre apartment, according to Deloitte's housing affordability survey released in 2021.

news.title: Gurugram civic body probe five years after road built on HSVP plots
news.para: A three-member committee has been constituted by MCG to find out how a road was constructed over HSVP plots in Sector 49. The road in question has affected at least eight plots of the HSVP, the market price of which is around Rs 24 crore.

news.title: ACC bags Kannur Limestone Block in Karnataka
news.para: ACC, a subsidiary of Swiss building material major Holcim group (earlier LafargeHolcim), had participated in an e-auction of the block, located in Kalburgi district of Karnataka.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespace to buy 9.24 acres land in Mumbai from M&M for Rs 365 crore
news.para: This new project will be Mahindra Lifespace's second residential development in Kandivali after its successful 'Mahindra Roots' project and will offer about 1 million square feet of carpet area.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body gives more time to 80 households to drain waste water into sewage
news.para: The municipal corporation (MC) has recently disconnected 12 connections, following which many people shifted their connections. For the few remaining, the MC has given time till February end to shift their connections.
